The 2021 Liechtenstein general election is scheduled to take place on February 7 (1). The country's statistics office has released its annual publication "Liechtenstein in Zahlen" (2). The election is being closely watched as it could result in a change in government (3). Other elections that have taken place in 2021 include the Georgia runoff election in the US (5,6) and Uganda's presidential election (8). In Africa, 10 presidential elections are also scheduled for 2021 (10). In the US, a bill was passed in North Carolina regarding calendar and election issues (11). The election in Liechtenstein has also resulted in the release of commemorative items (12). The candidates for the election have been finalized (13) and a summary of issues and judgments from previous elections have been released (14). In the US, there has been debate over the number of election lawsuits won by former President Trump (15). Relief efforts for Liechtenstein can also be found (16). Local government by-election results have been released in Trinidad and Tobago (17). Niger's presidential election was marred by irregularities (18).
